Any user thread blocked in `BufferPool.allocate()` waiting for memory, or a new `producer.send()` call arriving at this moment, can call `free.pollFirst()` and receive the just-freed buffer. This is especially likely under high throughput with `linger.ms > 0` (the condition stated in the bug report), because the accumulator is continuously receiving new messages.

